After circling enormous icebergs by boat and watching whales dive, we were dropped off on Quirpon island to hike through this dreamy landscape. The nearly six kilometre trail took us along cliff tops and rolling hills, we were surrounded by colourful vegetation, whales feeding in the ocean and even a little Arctic Fox came over to see who the visitors were.

Highly recommend this trip with @linkumtours! @gowesternnl #GoWesternNL

